summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Two Hundred Fifty ($250.00) Dollars out of the General Fund of the City of Seattle, to pay the claim of Mrs. Kate B. Marsh for personal injuries received by her on he 11th day of July, 1914, at the hour of eleven o'clock P.M., while walking on the sidewalk immediately in front of the store numbered 1413, on the south side of 70th Street, about half way between 14th Avenue Northwest and Alonzo Street, in the City of Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
